<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Iddings</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-26"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Dispatch about lynching received. Communicated contents to minister for
                            foreign affairs, who wishes me to thank the Government of the United
                            States for the same and to express his ardent wishes and his entire
                            confidence that all steps will be taken that can be, in the first
                            instance, to secure justice.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Iddings.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>